Monks/Sk/ Nc have Feigned death to do this<br>
&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;&gt;<br>
<br>
Velium Ring  -  Quest:   Garadain's War<br>
<br>
Estimated Time:&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Minimum Level:&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 55<br>
It is an all out war against Chief Ry'Gorr and his troops. <br>
<br>
Garadain says 'Very Well, Kaladur , give me the Adamantite ring and I will give you the marching orders. Once the orders are given to Gloradin in the next hut, we will be underway. You then must follow me to what will be our battleground. I must warn you, I will hold your ring until the head of Chief Ry'Gorr is given to me. If we fail, all will <br>
be lost... for both of us. <br>
<br>
As you can see, the 8th quest is tough. You only get ONE chance to do it right. Once you give Garadain your ring, you must kill Chief Ry'Gorr, loot his head, and give the head to Garadain. Ry'gorr only has a head during this event. I am unsure if you can do the quest if Garadain dies. Most likely, if he dies during this event you won't be able to complete the quest. You only get one shot at this, because you lose the ring. <br>
<br>
This battle involves 30+ rygorr, including some low 50's. This probably requires a well-tuned team of 55-60th level snare kiters, or alternatively a full 30+ PC army. <br>
<br>
The reward is the Velium Coldain Insignia Ring. &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
<br>
Velium Coldain Insignia Ring: <br>
AC: +8 Str: +8 Magic Resist: +8 , Weight: 0.1 , Classes / Race: All  , lore item magic item no drop, Triggred Effect: Shield of the Eighth [8 pt damage shield]<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
Alt Notes:<br>
When I was completing the eighth quest, here's what I did: <br>
<br>
I had two groups of people inside the courtyard, to include a 60 MNK and 55 DRU. They cleared the few mobs in the courtyard. Myself and my druid wife were outside and I turned in my 7th ring to Garadain. Garadain gave me orders to give to the female cleric in the other tent. I shouted a warning to the zone and promptly gave her the orders. (We DID NOT snarekite Garadain. You have what I consider ample amounts of time to get the head to Garadain before he charges the fort.) When I turned in the orders, the mobs spawned inside the Ry'Gorr courtyard. The 60 MNK pewled the Chief from the pack and they proceeded to slaughter him. Outside, my druid wife invised me and I ran into the fort to loot the head from the corpse. (I wasn't in the group that got the kill, so I had to wait even longer before the corpse was open to me for looting. I think I ate four or five of my fingernails waiting and constantly clicking.) Once I was able to loot the head, I got invised and ran back outside. <br>
<br>
Here's what most people DON'T know. (I had my wife watch Garadain and follow him while I was doing all this.) Garadain does NOT run straight for the fort. First, three packs of six KEWL looking soldiers form up. Garadain then calls them all together to one large group, which looked AWESOME. Garadain spent 1-2 minutes pep-talking them about how d0rfs ruled and giants sucked. This was when I turned the head into him and received my 8th ring. When I turned in the head and got my ring, Garadain despawned and left his d0rf army standing, waiting his order. The Ry'Gorr fort and its giants also did NOT despawn. <br>
<br>
It IS safe to give Garadain the Chief's head during his pep-talk to the Coldain army. <br>
<br>
THEORY: It might be possible that you wait for Garadain to give the actual &quot;CHARGE!&quot; orders. Then once the battle commences between them all, you hand Garadain the head and receive your ring. This way, the Coldain army beats the living poopie outta the Giants and cleans things out for the Ry'Gorr fort campers. <br>
